snippet.title: How to determine the missing measures of an isosceles trapezoid
snippet.description:
Learn how to solve problems about trapezoids. A trapezoid is a four sided shape (quadrilateral) such that one pair of opposite sides are parallel. Some of the properties of trapezoids are: one pair of opposite sides are parallel, etc. A trapezoid is isosceles is one pair of opposite sides are equal. A trapezoid is a right trapezoid if one of the angles is equal to 90 degrees.

Given expressions representing some of the parts of a parallelogram, we can evaluate the expressions using our knowledge of the properties of a parallelogram.
